.TH "snd_ac97_pcm_assign" 9 "snd_ac97_pcm_assign" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ac97_pcm_assign \- assign AC97 slots to given PCM streams
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_ac97_pcm_assign
.BI "(struct snd_ac97_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "unsigned short pcms_count "  ","
.BI "const struct ac97_pcm *pcms "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
the ac97 bus instance
.IP "pcms_count" 12
count of PCMs to be assigned
.IP "pcms" 12
PCMs to be assigned
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It assigns available AC97 slots for given PCMs. If none or only
some slots are available, pcm->xxx.slots and pcm->xxx.rslots[] members
are reduced and might be zero.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error code on failure.
